      <div class="sec-header">
        <div class="sec-num">04</div>
        <div class="sec-titles"><div class="sec-phase">Phase 4</div><div class="sec-title">Install Airbyte</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-head"><div class="step-n">1</div><div class="step-name">Run Airbyte Installation</div><span class="step-tag">~30 min</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <p class="step-desc">With a domain name (FQDN) — recommended:</p>
            <div class="code-wrap"><div class="code-top"><div class="code-dots"><span class="d1"></span><span class="d2"></span><span class="d3"></span></div><span class="code-lang">bash</span><button class="copy-btn" onclick="doCopy(this)">⎘ copy</button></div>
            <pre><span class="cf">abctl</span> local install <span class="cv">--host</span> airbyte.yourdomain.com</pre></div>
            <p class="step-desc">With only a Public IP (no domain):</p>
            <div class="code-wrap"><div class="code-top"><div class="code-dots"><span class="d1"></span><span class="d2"></span><span class="d3"></span></div><span class="code-lang">bash</span><button class="copy-btn" onclick="doCopy(this)">⎘ copy</button></div>
            <pre><span class="cf">abctl</span> local install <span class="cv">--host</span> &lt;ec2-public-ip&gt; <span class="cv">--insecure-cookies</span></pre></div>
            <div class="callout c-info"><span class="c-icon">⏳</span><span>This pulls all Docker images and sets up Kubernetes. Can take <strong>up to 30 minutes</strong>.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-head"><div class="step-n">2</div><div class="step-name">Check Installation Status</div><span class="step-tag">verify</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <div class="code-wrap"><div class="code-top"><div class="code-dots"><span class="d1"></span><span class="d2"></span><span class="d3"></span></div><span class="code-lang">bash</span><button class="copy-btn" onclick="doCopy(this)">⎘ copy</button></div>
            <pre><span class="cf">abctl</span> local status</pre></div>
            <div class="code-wrap"><div class="code-top"><div class="code-dots"><span class="d1"></span><span class="d2"></span><span class="d3"></span></div><span class="code-lang">output</span></div>
            <pre><span class="cm">Existing cluster 'airbyte-abctl' found</span>
<span class="cm">Found helm chart 'airbyte-abctl'</span>
<span class="cs">Status: deployed</span></pre></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-head"><div class="step-n">3</div><div class="step-name">Get Login Credentials</div><span class="step-tag">credentials</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <div class="code-wrap"><div class="code-top"><div class="code-dots"><span class="d1"></span><span class="d2"></span><span class="d3"></span></div><span class="code-lang">bash</span><button class="copy-btn" onclick="doCopy(this)">⎘ copy</button></div>
            <pre><span class="cf">abctl</span> local credentials</pre></div>
            <div class="callout c-warn"><span class="c-icon">📝</span><span>Save the printed <strong>Email</strong> and <strong>Password</strong> — you'll need them to log into the Airbyte UI.</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-head"><div class="step-n">4</div><div class="step-name">Access Airbyte UI in Browser</div><span class="step-tag">browser</span></div>
          <div class="step-body">
            <div class="code-wrap"><div class="code-top"><div class="code-dots"><span class="d1"></span><span class="d2"></span><span class="d3"></span></div><span class="code-lang">url</span><button class="copy-btn" onclick="doCopy(this)">⎘ copy</button></div>
            <pre><span class="cs">http://&lt;your-ec2-public-ip&gt;:8000</span>
<span class="cm">— or —</span>
<span class="cs">http://airbyte.yourdomain.com:8000</span></pre></div>
            <div class="callout c-ok"><span class="c-icon">🎉</span><span>Login with your credentials → Enter Organization name → Click <strong>Get Started</strong>. Airbyte is live!</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- 05 BACKEND -->
    <section id="backend">
      <div class="sec-header">
        <div class="sec-num">05</div>
        <div class="sec-titles"><div class="sec-phase">Deep Dive</div><div class="sec-title">What Happens on Backend</div></div>
      </div>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-line"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-connector"></div></div><div class="tl-card"><div class="tl-phase">Phase 1</div><div class="tl-title">🔍 Pre-flight Checks</div><div class="tl-desc">Verifies Docker is running, checks CPU / RAM / Disk availability, validates the --host flag, confirms port 8000 is free.</div></div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-line"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-connector"></div></div><div class="tl-card"><div class="tl-phase">Phase 2</div><div class="tl-title">🏗️ Kubernetes Cluster via kind</div><div class="tl-desc">Creates cluster named <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-abctl</code> inside Docker using kind. Saves kubeconfig to <code style="color:var(--cyan)">~/.airbyte/abctl/abctl.kubeconfig</code>.</div></div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-line"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-connector"></div></div><div class="tl-card"><div class="tl-phase">Phase 3</div><div class="tl-title">📦 Helm Charts Installed</div><div class="tl-desc">Installs Airbyte Helm Chart + NGINX Ingress Controller Helm Chart using the Helm package manager.</div></div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-line"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-connector"></div></div><div class="tl-card"><div class="tl-phase">Phase 4</div><div class="tl-title">🐳 Docker Images Downloaded</div><div class="tl-desc">Pulls: <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-server</code>, <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-webapp</code>, <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-worker</code>, <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-db</code>, <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-temporal</code>, <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-bootloader</code>.</div></div></div>
        <div class="tl-item"><div class="tl-line"><div class="tl-dot"></div><div class="tl-connector"></div></div><div class="tl-card"><div class="tl-phase">Phase 5</div><div class="tl-title">⚙️ Kubernetes Pods Start</div><div class="tl-desc">All components deployed as pods in namespace <code style="color:var(--cyan)">airbyte-abctl</code>. abctl waits for all pods to reach Running/Ready state.</div></div></div>
